Smithfield Foods, Inc. is based in Smithfield, VA and together with its subsidiaries, engages in production of hog, and processing of pork and beef worldwide. The company offers fresh pork and beef products. Smithfield Foods is also involved in turkey… MoreSmithfield Foods, Inc. is based in Smithfield, VA and together with its subsidiaries, engages in production of hog, and processing of pork and beef worldwide. The company offers fresh pork and beef products. Smithfield Foods is also involved in turkey production and hatchery operations.

Smithfield brands include Smithfield, John Morrell, Farmland Foods, Gwaltney, Patrick Cudahy, Krakus, Cook's Ham, and Stefano's.


 
Smithfield Foods, Inc. is based in Smithfield, VA and together with its subsidiaries, engages in production of hog, and processing of pork and beef worldwide. The company offers fresh pork and beef products. Smithfield Foods is also involved in turkey… MoreSmithfield Foods, Inc. is based in Smithfield, VA and together with its subsidiaries, engages in production of hog, and processing of pork and beef worldwide. The company offers fresh pork and beef products. Smithfield Foods is also involved in turkey production and hatchery operations.

Smithfield brands include Smithfield, John Morrell, Farmland Foods, Gwaltney, Patrick Cudahy, Krakus, Cook's Ham, and Stefano's.

•Smithfield Foods was bought by Shuanghui International for $4.7B.  The IT department is currently transitioning outsourcing partners from Capgemini to Fujitsu.
•The Corporate IT department for Smithfield Foods, Inc. is largely outsourced, including systems, infrastructure, and SAP development.
•Smithfield Foods utilizes an SAP ERP platform, support for which is largely outsourced.  
•Subsidiary companies Armour-Eckrich Meatsand Murphy-Brown, LLC maintain independent IT departments, though they receive most of their technology direction from the corporate headquarters office.

